      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That heavy feeling often comes from weighing the grandeur of history against the weight of unfulfilled personal needs, and it is completely reasonable to feel exhausted after exhausting the map. Perhaps the \"exit sign\" you seek is not merely the end of travel, but a signal to finally pause, breathe, and rewrite your own story in your own time. Just as Rome stood still for us so we could be still with ourselves, today's silence belongs to a new chapter that matters more than the next sight you have to see.",
      "source": "target",
